{
  "word": "expert",
  "wordRoot": [
    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#14087\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">expert</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>14世纪晚期，“有经验的； 熟练的”，源自古法语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">expert</span>， <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">espert</span> “有经验的，熟练的”，直接源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">expertus</span>（缩写自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">*experitus</span>），“经过尝试、证明、经验所知的”， <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">experiri</span> 的过去分词，“尝试，测试”，源自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">ex</span> “出”（见 <a href=\"/cn/word/ex-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ex- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">ex-</a>）+ <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">peritus</span> “有经验的，经过测试的”，源自 PIE <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">*per-yo-</span>， <a href=\"/cn/word/*per-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *per- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*per-</a>（3）的带后缀形式，“尝试，冒险”。形容词倾向于在第二个音节上重读，名词则在第一个音节上重读。相关词汇： <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">Expertly</span>； <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">expertness</span>。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>"
    },
    {
      "title": "<h2 id=\"#50407\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\">expert<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div></h2>",
      "html": "<p>15世纪初，“经验丰富的人”，来自 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of expert \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/expert\">expert</a>（形容词）。这个词在1825年以法律意义重新出现，“指那些凭借特殊的学识或经验，对于一般人不了解的某一主题，可以在法庭上就其意见作证的人，与普通证人相区别，后者通常只能就事实作证”[世纪词典]。</p>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "expertise<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>\"专家的质量或状态\"，1868年，来自法语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">expertise</i>（16世纪）\"专家评估，专家报告\"，源自 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">expert</i>（见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of expert \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/expert\">expert</a>（形容词））。更早且更英式的说法是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">expertness</i>（约1600年）。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "experto crede<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\"></div>",
      "html": "<p>拉丁语，“从一个知道的人那里拿”（“埃涅阿斯纪”，xi.283）； <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">expertus</i> 的单数与格（参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of expert \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/expert\">expert</a>（形容词））+ <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">credere</i> 的祈使语单数“相信”（参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of credo \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/credo\">credo</a>）。</p>"
    }
  ]
}